WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-US

00:00:02.600 --> 00:00:06.666
How to fight against the yellowness and dullness that are unique to Asians?

00:00:06.700 --> 00:00:08.900
Some people say I can use VC,

00:00:08.900 --> 00:00:10.666
but after using it, 

00:00:10.666 --> 00:00:13.700
my skin becomes even more yellow. Some people say I can use niacinamide,

00:00:13.700 --> 00:00:15.266
but it turns out that it’s not the right approach.

00:00:15.366 --> 00:00:16.200
Some people say

00:00:16.200 --> 00:00:19.666
that yellowness and dullness are unique to old people.

00:00:19.666 --> 00:00:20.700
I’m young now,

00:00:20.700 --> 00:00:22.466
so I can’t use it. 

00:00:22.466 --> 00:00:23.400
That’s not true.

00:00:23.400 --> 00:00:25.433
If you don’t take care of yourself right,

00:00:25.433 --> 00:00:26.266
young people

00:00:26.266 --> 00:00:27.733
will also have dullness.

00:00:27.833 --> 00:00:28.800
In this issue,

00:00:28.800 --> 00:00:32.000
we will do a special topic

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:35.000
on skin care. Where does this yellowness come from and where

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:36.933
should we let it go ?

00:00:36.933 --> 00:00:39.400
We will conduct a systematic analysis

00:00:39.400 --> 00:00:42.133
to help everyone avoid detours

00:00:42.133 --> 00:00:43.333
on the road to whitening and beauty.

00:00:50.266 --> 00:00:50.866
First of all,

00:00:50.866 --> 00:00:54.300
where does this yellowness and dullness come from?

00:00:54.400 --> 00:00:57.433
Some people say it is because Some say it's because of too much melanin.

00:00:57.466 --> 00:00:58.466
Some say

00:00:58.466 --> 00:01:00.700
it's because of too many free radicals

00:01:00.700 --> 00:01:02.100
, so the collagen denatures and the

00:01:02.100 --> 00:01:03.300
skin becomes less transparent.

00:01:03.300 --> 00:01:05.633
Some say it's because of drinking too much milk tea,

00:01:05.633 --> 00:01:07.733
which results in the face being glycated.

00:01:07.733 --> 00:01:10.066
All of the above opinions

00:01:10.066 --> 00:01:12.800
are correct, but not complete.

00:01:12.800 --> 00:01:14.833
The overall color of our skin

00:01:14.833 --> 00:01:18.666
is determined by three parts: skin color, uniformity of refractive index

00:01:18.666 --> 00:01:21.333
, and scattering of the skin surface

00:01:21.433 --> 00:01:23.033
. First of all

00:01:23.033 --> 00:01:25.000
, skin color is the color of the skin.

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:27.833
This color is determined by two pigments.

00:01:27.833 --> 00:01:29.933
One is called eumelanin, which

00:01:29.933 --> 00:01:31.266
dominates dark skin.

00:01:31.266 --> 00:01:32.633
For example, Africans

00:01:32.633 --> 00:01:35.200
have a higher eumelanin content.

00:01:35.333 --> 00:01:36.300
The other

00:01:36.300 --> 00:01:37.733
is called pheomelanin,

00:01:37.733 --> 00:01:39.233
which dominates light skin.

00:01:39.233 --> 00:01:41.333
For example, Europeans have a higher skin content. Whiter

00:01:41.333 --> 00:01:43.233
skin is mainly composed of pheomelanin, with

00:01:43.233 --> 00:01:44.600
very little eumelanin.

00:01:44.600 --> 00:01:45.933
Asians

00:01:45.933 --> 00:01:47.333
have both eumelanin and

00:01:47.333 --> 00:01:48.333
pheomelanin in

00:01:48.333 --> 00:01:49.300
different ratios,

00:01:49.300 --> 00:01:52.400
resulting in different skin tones.

00:01:52.500 --> 00:01:54.633
So, today's topic

00:01:54.633 --> 00:01:57.933
isn't about the yellowish color of Asians. Where does it come from?

00:01:57.933 --> 00:02:01.200
Pheomelanin is one of the key factors,

00:02:01.200 --> 00:02:02.000
as it

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:06.133
not only dominates lighter skin tones like yellow, but also

00:02:06.133 --> 00:02:07.933
makes your skin uglier

00:02:07.933 --> 00:02:09.833
through oxidation.

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:10.900
Secondly,

00:02:10.900 --> 00:02:13.700
let's talk about the uniformity of the skin's

00:02:13.700 --> 00:02:15.400
refractive index.

00:02:15.433 --> 00:02:16.233
Refractive index,

00:02:16.233 --> 00:02:17.700
as defined in physics,

00:02:17.700 --> 00:02:22.066
refers to the speed difference of light passing through different media.

00:02:22.066 --> 00:02:22.633
For example,

00:02:22.633 --> 00:02:23.700
this is a chopstick

00:02:23.700 --> 00:02:25.033
in the air. In the air,

00:02:25.033 --> 00:02:26.233
it looks straight and

00:02:26.233 --> 00:02:27.066
clear.

00:02:27.066 --> 00:02:30.200
But if we pour water into it,

00:02:30.200 --> 00:02:32.233
we can see that the chopsticks bend.

00:02:32.233 --> 00:02:33.200
Why do they bend?

00:02:33.200 --> 00:02:35.100
It is because the refractive index in water

00:02:35.100 --> 00:02:37.866
is different from that in air.

00:02:37.933 --> 00:02:39.100
Imagine

00:02:39.100 --> 00:02:41.733
what would happen

00:02:41.733 --> 00:02:42.666
if I put a handful of soil in the water.

00:02:42.733 --> 00:02:44.233
The water would become turbid

00:02:44.233 --> 00:02:46.233
and we would not be able to see the chopsticks.

00:02:46.233 --> 00:02:48.433
Our skin is actually the same.

00:02:48.433 --> 00:02:52.533
Our dermis contains about 70%-80% water.

00:02:52.533 --> 00:02:53.700
The rest of the substances

00:02:53.700 --> 00:02:55.733
are mainly composed of substances such as collagen and hyaluronic

00:02:55.733 --> 00:02:56.666
acid that

00:02:56.666 --> 00:02:59.833
can combine with water.

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:02.133
When hyaluronic acid and collagen

00:03:02.133 --> 00:03:03.733
grab water molecules

00:03:03.733 --> 00:03:06.800
, they will be in the skin. Forming such a

00:03:06.800 --> 00:03:07.700
relatively uniform

00:03:07.700 --> 00:03:10.333
system will make our skin look more transparent.

00:03:10.333 --> 00:03:12.266
However, when your skin is dehydrated

00:03:12.266 --> 00:03:15.033
or your collagen and hyaluronic acid are lost,

00:03:15.033 --> 00:03:17.800
its refractive index will be very uneven,

00:03:17.800 --> 00:03:20.266
and our skin transparency will decrease

00:03:20.266 --> 00:03:21.666
and the skin will become darker.

00:03:21.900 --> 00:03:24.500
Having talked about the pigmentation problem

00:03:24.500 --> 00:03:25.866
and the light-blocking rate problem in the skin,

00:03:25.866 --> 00:03:29.333
let's talk about the scattering rate of the skin surface.

00:03:29.333 --> 00:03:30.866
What does it affect

00:03:30.866 --> 00:03:31.833
? ​​Scattering

00:03:31.833 --> 00:03:32.533
rate,

00:03:32.533 --> 00:03:34.933
as the name suggests , is a state of

00:03:34.933 --> 00:03:36.666
diffuse reflection

00:03:36.666 --> 00:03:38.633
when light hits the skin surface.

00:03:38.633 --> 00:03:41.100
When our skin is rough,

00:03:41.100 --> 00:03:42.133
has various textures

00:03:42.133 --> 00:03:43.500
, and is thicker in cuticle,

00:03:43.500 --> 00:03:45.466
the degree of scattering will be more chaotic.

00:03:45.466 --> 00:03:47.900
Our skin It looks dull.

00:03:47.900 --> 00:03:48.600
For example, if you

00:03:48.600 --> 00:03:49.866
apply a layer of foundation

00:03:49.866 --> 00:03:52.866
, we fill in the rough textures and

00:03:52.866 --> 00:03:54.933
your skin looks bright

00:03:54.933 --> 00:03:57.833
because the reflection becomes even.

00:03:57.833 --> 00:04:00.433
But too even is not good.

00:04:00.433 --> 00:04:01.600
For example, if you have oily skin

00:04:01.600 --> 00:04:02.733
and produce a lot of oil

00:04:02.733 --> 00:04:04.800
, your face will look shiny.

00:04:04.800 --> 00:04:06.466
This is called mirror reflection.

00:04:06.466 --> 00:04:09.800
Mirror reflection makes people look dirty.

00:04:09.800 --> 00:04:11.100
This is not good either.

00:04:12.100 --> 00:04:14.666
Let's start with these three parts

00:04:14.666 --> 00:04:18.100
to tell you how to improve yellowness and dullness.

00:04:18.133 --> 00:04:20.133
First of all, the first skin color problem

00:04:20.133 --> 00:04:23.100
is nothing more than sun protection and whitening.

00:04:23.100 --> 00:04:25.666
There are two things that people easily overlook.

00:04:25.666 --> 00:04:27.666
I want to tell you in particular

00:04:27.666 --> 00:04:30.933
that post-sun cleaning and post-sun repair

00:04:30.933 --> 00:04:32.900
may be the same as sun protection. Why is

00:04:32.900 --> 00:04:35.400
post-sun cleaning so important?

00:04:35.400 --> 00:04:37.333
Some waterproof and high-factor sunscreens

00:04:37.333 --> 00:04:40.433
cannot be cleaned off even with facial cleansers.

00:04:40.466 --> 00:04:41.866
When they cannot be cleaned off,

00:04:41.866 --> 00:04:44.266
they will remain on your face and oxidize

00:04:44.266 --> 00:04:46.500
. After oxidation, they will irritate your skin

00:04:46.500 --> 00:04:48.700
and produce more melanin.

00:04:48.700 --> 00:04:50.933
Wouldn't that mean your skin will be whitened?

00:04:51.233 --> 00:04:52.833
The key to post-sun repair

00:04:52.833 --> 00:04:55.533
is soothing and cooling after

00:04:55.533 --> 00:04:57.000
sun exposure

00:04:57.000 --> 00:04:58.833
. Because in the summer,

00:04:58.833 --> 00:05:01.933
in addition to ultraviolet radiation, we are

00:05:01.933 --> 00:05:04.700
also exposed to infrared radiation

00:05:04.733 --> 00:05:07.433
. Infrared radiation will heat our skin

00:05:07.433 --> 00:05:10.333
, and this heat will continue

00:05:10.333 --> 00:05:12.433
after you go indoors after

00:05:12.433 --> 00:05:13.833
sun exposure

00:05:13.933 --> 00:05:17.666
as long as your skin temperature does not drop. This heating will also promote the production of melanin and

00:05:17.666 --> 00:05:19.633
make you darker again.

00:05:19.633 --> 00:05:21.900
So when we

00:05:21.900 --> 00:05:22.900
return home after a day's trip,

00:05:22.900 --> 00:05:23.800
the first thing

00:05:23.800 --> 00:05:26.300
to do is to wash off our sunscreen.

00:05:26.300 --> 00:05:27.266
After washing it off,

00:05:27.266 --> 00:05:30.866
let your skin cool down and soothe.

00:05:30.866 --> 00:05:32.466
Only by doing these two actions

00:05:32.466 --> 00:05:35.533
can you lay a good foundation for the subsequent whitening.

00:05:35.800 --> 00:05:37.200
How to choose

00:05:37.200 --> 00:05:39.000
products for skin color problems? For recommendations on sunscreen,

00:05:39.000 --> 00:05:39.900
you can refer to

00:05:39.900 --> 00:05:42.033
the sunscreens I mentioned

00:05:42.033 --> 00:05:43.866
in my previous sunscreen special.

00:05:43.900 --> 00:05:45.800
As for products for cleaning sunscreen,

00:05:45.800 --> 00:05:48.933
if you choose waterproof sunscreen or high-factor sunscreen,

00:05:48.933 --> 00:05:51.700
I recommend that you use makeup remover to wash it off

00:05:51.700 --> 00:05:54.333
, such as Shu Uemura's Amber Cleansing Oil

00:05:54.333 --> 00:05:55.666
Bobbi Brown makeup remover oil

00:05:55.666 --> 00:05:58.666
and Farmacy makeup remover balm, etc.

00:05:58.833 --> 00:06:01.333
If it is a low-factor commuting sunscreen

00:06:01.333 --> 00:06:02.800
and not waterproof,

00:06:02.800 --> 00:06:04.733
you can use facial cleanser to wash it off,

00:06:04.800 --> 00:06:07.066
such as Freeplus Amino Acid Facial Cleanser

00:06:07.066 --> 00:06:09.266
or Paula's Choice Green Snot Facial Cleanser.

00:06:09.266 --> 00:06:10.333
These can be used

00:06:10.633 --> 00:06:12.000
for after-sun repair products.

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:13.033
There are mainly two

00:06:13.033 --> 00:06:14.133
types. One is a large spray,

00:06:14.133 --> 00:06:15.333
such as La Roche-Posay Large Spray and

00:06:15.333 --> 00:06:16.266
Avène Large Spray.

00:06:16.266 --> 00:06:17.933
The other is a mask

00:06:17.933 --> 00:06:19.533
, such as La Roche-Posay B5 Mask and

00:06:19.533 --> 00:06:21.300
Eucerin Mask. These can all be used

00:06:21.533 --> 00:06:23.000
for cooling after sun exposure.

00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:25.733
I recommend the hydrogel-type fever-reducing patch.

00:06:25.733 --> 00:06:27.266
It is relatively cheap

00:06:27.266 --> 00:06:27.866
and practical.

00:06:27.866 --> 00:06:29.500
The temperature is neither too hot nor too cold,

00:06:29.500 --> 00:06:31.100
just right. I

00:06:31.100 --> 00:06:32.500
have to remind everyone here

00:06:32.500 --> 00:06:34.066
that when you are sweating and

00:06:34.066 --> 00:06:35.600
your pores are open,

00:06:35.600 --> 00:06:38.900
do not use iced masks or large sprays to cool down,

00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:41.700
as this will cause new stimulation to the skin . It is better

00:06:42.033 --> 00:06:43.733
to have adequate sun protection.

00:06:43.733 --> 00:06:44.666
For whitening

00:06:44.666 --> 00:06:49.000
, refer to the 16-type whitening method we talked about before.

00:06:49.000 --> 00:06:51.700
In fact, among the 16-type whitening method we talked about before,

00:06:51.700 --> 00:06:54.466
there is a special type.

00:06:54.466 --> 00:06:56.266
It is the dull type.

00:06:56.300 --> 00:06:58.933
When we talked about the dull type before,

00:06:58.933 --> 00:07:01.000
we said that when choosing products and ingredients, we

00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:03.233
should focus on

00:07:03.233 --> 00:07:06.200
the four anti-oxidation, anti-glycation, anti-glycosylation and anti-blue light.

00:07:06.200 --> 00:07:07.133
In this way,

00:07:07.133 --> 00:07:10.733
the two major internal factors that affect our yellowness and dullness

00:07:10.733 --> 00:07:12.166
are solved together. For

00:07:12.166 --> 00:07:13.266
suitable products,

00:07:13.266 --> 00:07:16.600
you can refer to all the products involved

00:07:16.600 --> 00:07:18.500
in the 16-type whitening method I mentioned before.

00:07:18.500 --> 00:07:19.633
I will also

00:07:19.633 --> 00:07:21.000
put them at the end of the video.

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:23.266
You can take screenshots for reference and collection.

00:07:23.833 --> 00:07:26.866
The third part is to improve the scattering rate of the skin surface.

00:07:26.866 --> 00:07:30.266
Its main method is to make the cuticle smooth.

00:07:30.266 --> 00:07:31.033
There is also a hidden point

00:07:31.033 --> 00:07:33.133
here.

00:07:33.133 --> 00:07:35.400
In fact, our stratum corneum

00:07:35.400 --> 00:07:37.100
also contains There is melanin,

00:07:37.100 --> 00:07:39.733
and when you properly exfoliate,

00:07:39.733 --> 00:07:41.500
not only can you smooth the skin

00:07:41.500 --> 00:07:42.733
texture,

00:07:42.766 --> 00:07:44.900
but you can also let some excess

00:07:44.900 --> 00:07:47.333
useless melanin leave your body,

00:07:47.333 --> 00:07:48.900
making you look whiter.

00:07:49.033 --> 00:07:50.266
When it comes to exfoliation,

00:07:50.266 --> 00:07:52.633
the most well-known method is to use acid.

00:07:52.666 --> 00:07:54.100
There are many kinds of

00:07:54.100 --> 00:07:54.900
acids on the market

00:07:54.900 --> 00:07:57.600
, such as glycolic acid, mandelic acid, and lactic acid

00:07:57.600 --> 00:07:59.600
, which are called first-generation fruit acids,

00:07:59.600 --> 00:08:00.866
and gluconolactone, lactobionic acid, and

00:08:00.866 --> 00:08:02.433
maltobionic acid,

00:08:02.433 --> 00:08:04.533
which are second-, third-, and fourth-generation fruit acids.

00:08:04.533 --> 00:08:07.700
Although they can all soften and exfoliate

00:08:07.700 --> 00:08:10.866
, their exfoliating abilities are different.

00:08:10.866 --> 00:08:13.100
For example, the first-generation fruit acid is the strongest,

00:08:13.100 --> 00:08:15.233
especially glycolic acid and mandelic acid , which are very strong,

00:08:15.233 --> 00:08:16.533
while the second, third, and fourth-generation

00:08:16.533 --> 00:08:18.466
fruit acids are also very strong . Fourth-generation glycolic acids

00:08:18.466 --> 00:08:20.533
have weaker exfoliating abilities

00:08:20.533 --> 00:08:21.800
, but they are gentler and

00:08:21.800 --> 00:08:22.966
more moisturizing.

00:08:22.966 --> 00:08:24.800
So when choosing products,

00:08:24.800 --> 00:08:26.400
if your skin is sensitive

00:08:26.400 --> 00:08:27.266
or dry

00:08:27.266 --> 00:08:28.466
, you should

00:08:28.466 --> 00:08:30.666
choose from second-, third-, and fourth-generation glycolic acids.

00:08:30.666 --> 00:08:32.400
If your skin is oily

00:08:32.400 --> 00:08:35.333
and thick, you can

00:08:35.333 --> 00:08:38.666
choose from first-generation glycolic acids, especially glycolic acid and mandelic acid.

00:08:38.900 --> 00:08:40.133
In addition to acids,

00:08:40.133 --> 00:08:42.266
there is another type of product that can exfoliate

00:08:42.266 --> 00:08:43.800
, and that is protease.

00:08:43.866 --> 00:08:45.666
It is written in the formula sheet and is

00:08:45.666 --> 00:08:47.466
generally called keratinase,

00:08:47.466 --> 00:08:49.866
papain, or bromelain.

00:08:49.933 --> 00:08:51.200
These proteases

00:08:51.200 --> 00:08:54.866
also have the ability to exfoliate and soften keratin,

00:08:54.866 --> 00:08:55.600
but they

00:08:55.600 --> 00:08:57.033
are less irritating

00:08:57.100 --> 00:08:59.000
and more suitable for people with more sensitive and

00:08:59.000 --> 00:09:00.633
drier skin.

00:09:00.633 --> 00:09:02.600
However, whether it is an acid product

00:09:02.600 --> 00:09:03.733
or an enzyme product,

00:09:03.733 --> 00:09:05.266
you must pay attention to

00:09:05.266 --> 00:09:06.200
the frequency of

00:09:06.200 --> 00:09:08.400
use .

00:09:08.433 --> 00:09:10.033
The frequency I recommend is

00:09:10.033 --> 00:09:12.066
about 1 to 2 times a week.

00:09:12.066 --> 00:09:13.333
I will post the products involved

00:09:13.333 --> 00:09:15.233
at the end of the video

00:09:15.233 --> 00:09:17.266
for your reference and collection.

